Southeast Asset Advisors Inc. Continues to Hold Stake in CSX Corporation (CSX)






28 July 2017, 07:52 | Justin Tyler




Finally, Two Sigma Securities LLC acquired a new position in shares of CSX Corporation during the first quarter worth about $796,000. Clinton Group Inc.'s holdings in CSX Corporation were worth $10,154,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period.Hedge funds and other institutional investors have recently added to or reduced their stakes in the company. CSX Corporation makes up 1.5% of Mckinley Capital Management LLC Delaware's holdings, making the stock its 16th largest position. Vanguard Group Inc. boosted its stake in shares of CSX Corporation by 0.5% in the first quarter. Bank of New York Mellon Corp boosted its stake in shares of CSX Corporation by 22.3% in the first quarter. Janus Capital Management LLC now owns 16,620,538 shares of the transportation company's stock worth $773,686,000 after buying an additional 4,114,395 shares during the period. R. G. Niederhoffer Capital Management Inc. bought a new stake in shares of CSX Corporation during the first quarter worth $527,000. Under Armour, Inc. has 5 buy ratings, 18 holds and 2 sells even after the stock tumbled -59.13% from its high of $42.94 to a $0 market value through last close. State of Alaska Department of Revenue acquired a new position in shares of CSX Corporation during the first quarter worth $375,000. Stock Yards Bank & Trust Co. now owns 8,032 shares of the transportation company's stock valued at $374,000 after buying an additional 53 shares during the period.Shares of CSX Corporation (NASDAQ CSX) traded down 3.96% on Friday, reaching $50.00. These ratios are important while doing valuation of the company or the shares of the company. CSX Corporation has a 1-year low of $27.46 and a 1-year high of $55.48. The average volume of a stock suggests the liquidity of a particular company.The company's P/E ratio is 27.23 and market cap is 47.55B.CSX Corporation (NASDAQ:CSX) last announced its earnings results on Tuesday, July 18th.An earnings forecast is an analyst's outlook for a company's future quarterly or annual earnings. The business had revenue of $2.93 billion during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $2.85 billion. CSX Corporation had a return on equity of 15.67% and a net margin of 15.19%. During the same period previous year, the company earned $0.47 earnings per share. This repurchase authorization authorizes the transportation company to buy up to 2.2% of its stock through open market purchases. Shares repurchase plans are generally an indication that the company's management believes its shares are undervalued.

Energy Transfer Equity, LP (ETE) stock attained 10.77% Yearly return

